</span><hr size=1> Are you referring to just on the platform in the arena zone?  If so...that's really a pain the ass vs. a melee.  But in the big circle that is pvp grounds there are a few things that will help you out.  Many i know use levitate and the throne roof and/or pillars, it's kinda lame, but at least you can get some leverage and make it harder for them to find you.  Use shadowstep/yonder a lot...the thing that sucks is they will usually have a visual on you fast since it's an open area, and even if you start spamming your nuke gem so it casts the second they are in range, they still bash you a second before you finish casting.  For this, I would suggest getting a focus ring to speed up casting, that and/or train in Quick Damage.  This should allow you to cast from max range before they get to you.  Then shadowstep/yonder till you have distance again and repeat.  That's all I can suggest really, remember to kill them fast!  Don't let them run around and regen with fungi, then they kite you =p.<br><br>Thanatopsis of the Nexus<br>Sorcerer of Vae Inimicus<br>Tunare Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=75.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=75.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=75.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=75.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=htt